{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.15.1515;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\b\f0\fs20 Often data to be merged is simple tabular data. For instance, in our address book data, each contact may have multiple addresses and phones.\par
\par
In these sorts of merges, multiple tasks need to be used to handle the repeating data. This is accomplished by using one task for the "header" data, and subtasks for the repeating data, somewhat as is done for displaying subform data.\par
